---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { PROFILE } from '../data/profile';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="Pete Ghiorse leads AI/ML products, builds production agents, and publishes rigorous evaluations of how they behave."
  ogImage="/images/profile/pete-ghiorse-profile-card.png"
  ogImageAlt="About Pete Ghiorse, AI/ML product leader and founder"
>
  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-16 md:py-24">
    <p class="text-(--color-primary) font-semibold text-sm tracking-widest uppercase mb-4 animate-fade-up">About</p>
    <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-extrabold mb-10 animate-fade-up stagger-1">
      What I lead, what I build, and <span class="gradient-text">how I test it</span>
    </h1>

    <div class="space-y-6 text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 leading-relaxed animate-fade-up stagger-2">
      <p class="text-xl text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-200">
        {PROFILE.oneLine}
      </p>

      <p>
        I’m a <strong class="text-slate-900 dark:text-white font-semibold">Group Product Manager for AI/ML at Capital One</strong>, where I lead product direction for ML-powered spend controls and fraud detection. I’m also the founder of <strong class="text-slate-900 dark:text-white font-semibold">Honeydew</strong>, a production family-coordination agent I began building in 2025.
      </p>

      <p>
        Before that, I co-founded <strong class="text-slate-900 dark:text-white font-semibold">GiveTide</strong>, ran it for five years, and sold it in 2022. That arc—from founder to enterprise product leadership and back to hands-on building—is why I care about both the strategic decision and the behavior of the system underneath it.
      </p>

      <p>
        I’m based in New York City and open to regular Bay Area travel for the right role.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white pt-4">The product questions</h2>

      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        {[
          { title: 'Decision boundaries', desc: 'What should the system do, when should it ask, and what should it never guess?' },
          { title: 'Evidence over demos', desc: 'What happens on repeated, messy, or irreversible cases—not just the best prompt in the deck?' },
          { title: 'Operating trust', desc: 'How do product policy, interface design, and model behavior reinforce one another in production?' },
          { title: 'Useful economics', desc: 'Where does cheaper intelligence change the product, the team, or the business model—and where does it not?' },
        ].map(item => (
          <div class="p-4 rounded-xl bg-slate-50 dark:bg-[#141b2d] border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800">
            <p class="font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-1">{item.title}</p>
            <p class="text-sm">{item.desc}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>

      <h2 id="practice" class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white pt-4 scroll-mt-24">How I keep my skills current</h2>

      <p>
        My loop is <strong class="text-slate-900 dark:text-white font-semibold">{PROFILE.practiceLoop.join(' → ')}</strong>. I start with a real operating problem, instrument the behavior, turn failures into evaluation cases, and revise the product before I write the conclusion.
      </p>

      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        {PROFILE.focusAreas.map(item => (
          <div class="p-4 rounded-xl bg-slate-50 dark:bg-[#141b2d] border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800">
            <p class="font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-1">{item.title}</p>
            <p class="text-sm">{item.description}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-2 border-(--color-primary) pl-6 py-2 my-8">
        <p class="text-slate-900 dark:text-white font-medium">{PROFILE.qualityStatement}</p>
      </div>

      <p>
        The standard is visible in the work: methods and limitations sit beside results; private user data stays out of public research; corrections remain visible; and conclusions narrow when the evidence is thinner than the first draft suggested.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white pt-4">Background</h2>

      <p>
        I earned a <strong class="text-slate-900 dark:text-white font-semibold">B.S. in Finance &amp; Economics</strong> from the <strong class="text-slate-900 dark:text-white font-semibold">University of Richmond</strong>, graduating Magna Cum Laude. My career has moved through fintech, fraud systems, consumer software, and the practical limits of AI agents.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-10 p-6 rounded-2xl bg-slate-50 dark:bg-[#141b2d] border border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-800">
        <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-(--color-primary) tracking-widest uppercase mb-2">{PROFILE.publication.name}</p>
        <p class="font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-2">Research editions and essays</p>
        <p class="text-sm mb-4">{PROFILE.publication.description}</p>
        <a href="https://peterghiorse.substack.com/subscribe?utm_source=peterghiorse.com&utm_medium=website&utm_campaign=content_distribution&utm_content=about_chatgpete" target="_blank" rel="noopener" data-newsletter-cta data-newsletter-impression data-analytics-placement="about_chatgpete" class="text-(--color-primary) font-semibold hover:underline">Subscribe to ChatGPeTe &rarr;</a>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-6 p-6 rounded-2xl border border-blue-200 dark:border-blue-900 bg-blue-50/70 dark:bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-2">For recruiters and hiring leaders</p>
        <p class="text-sm mb-4">{PROFILE.recruiterFocus}</p>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-5 text-sm font-semibold">
          <a href="/resume.pdf" data-profile-cta="resume_download" data-analytics-placement="about" class="text-(--color-primary) hover:underline">Download résumé &rarr;</a>
          <a href="/projects" data-profile-cta="selected_work" data-analytics-placement="about" class="text-(--color-primary) hover:underline">Inspect selected work &rarr;</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
